{"lemma":"بَرْذَعَةُ","slug":"بَرْذَعَةُ","root":"ب.ر.ذ.ع","root_slug":"ب-ر-ذ-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ذ-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2246"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%B0%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"packsaddle","examples":[{"text":"ثم كتب إليه عمر أن تختم في رقاب أهل الذمة بالرصاص، ويظهروا مناطقهم، ويجزوا نواصيهم، ويركبوا على الأكف - جمع أكاف وهو البردعة - عرضًا، ولا يضربوا الجزية إلا على من جرت عليه المواسي، ولا يضربوا على النساء، ولا على الولدان ولا يتشبهوا بالمسلمين."}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Partav, Barda (A city in Azerbaijan)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Middle Persian [script needed] (bwlytn' /⁠burīdan⁠/, “cutting”) originally referring to scrap fabrics packed under a saddlebag; compare Armenian բուրդ (burd, “wool”), Georgian ბურდო (burdo, “chaff”), Sanskrit वर्धक (vardhaka, “shearing, cutting; carpenter”); ultimately from Proto-Indo-European *bʰerdʰ- (“cut”).\n\nBorrowed from Old Armenian Պարտաւ (Partaw)."},"ipa":["/bar.ða.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2246","headword_ar":"بَرْذَعَةٌ","root":"br*E","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodaEapN","text_ar":"بَرْدَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cloth of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hilos","text_ar":"حِلْس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is put beneath the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA*iEu","text_ar":"بَرَاذِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAdiEu","text_ar":"بَرَادِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) Ru-beh says, [using the sing. without the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a coll. gen. n.,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      wa taHota A^aHonaA='i Alr~iHaAli Albaro*aEu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And beneath the curved pieces of wood of the camels' saddles are the bardha'ahs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  This is the primary signification: but in the conventional language of our time, it is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ass's saddle; the thing upon which one rides on an ass, like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saroj","text_ar":"سَرْج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffed saddle; generally stuffed with straw; and used for a mule as well as for an ass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or an ass's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br*Ep","text_ar":"برذعة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a saddle like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAfN","text_ar":"اـِكَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baro*aEapN","text_ar":"بَرْذَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land which is neither hard nor soft:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl. as above. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}